We're back with a brand new episode of Alphabetti and this week it's duck'in ravioli.

@hughwoodward - Duck confit is high up on the list of my dessert island ingredients. 

Stick it in bouncy ravioli, cover it with a creamy sauce and we are talking absolute food paradise. Join me on my journey to find out how to do it!🦆🍝

node.text:
Chicken 'cordon bleu' is French for Chicken 'blue ribbon', which is potentially confusing. It also has nothing to do with the famous Cordon Bleu cookery school. Despite these mysterious origins, the concept of deep fried, rolled chicken breast with ham and cheese has international appeal (why wouldn't it). We're taking a new slant on this erroneously monikered dish - introducing it to a wonderful, creamy pasta and adding parmesan - sorry Italy!

INGREDIENTS
2 chicken breasts
Plain flour
Beaten eggs
Panko bread crumbs
1 tbsp butter
3 cloves garlic
300ml double cream
200g gruyere
1/2 cup parmesan
200g chopped ham
1 tbsp dijon mustard
Seasoning
500g cooked penne

INGREDIENTS
Dough
190ml milk, lukewarm
50g sugar
1 tsp active dry yeast
3 medium eggs
1 tsp vanilla essence
500g all-purpose flour, plus for dusting
1 tsp salt
75g butter, softened
Toasted Pecans
75g pecans
2 tbsp butter
200g pecan nuts, chopped
Caramel
300g dark brown sugar
4 tbsp butter
200ml single cream
Apple Filling 
4 medium apples, very finely diced
3 Tablespoons water
2 Tablespoons butter
1 teaspoon cinnamon
1/3 cup sugar
1 Tablespoon + 1 teaspoon cornstarch
2 Tablespoons water
 Apple Cinnamon Sugar
100g sugar
2 tbsp cinnamon
3 tbsp blitzed apple crisps
